# Lumen Backend

FastAPI service for the Lumen journaling PWA. Phase 1 scaffold complete.
Runs in Docker (lumen-api, port 8000). Connects to Supabase via Python client.

## Stack
- Python 3.11, FastAPI, Supabase Python client, PyJWT, Pydantic v2
- No ORM — Supabase client directly
- No TypeScript, no local installs — Docker only

## File Map
- `app/main.py` — app init, CORS, router mount, /health
- `app/auth.py` — `get_current_user` dependency: verifies JWT, returns user_id (sub claim)
- `app/routes/entries.py` — CRUD for /entries
- `app/models/entry.py` — EntryCreate, EntryUpdate, EntryResponse

## Auth
Every protected route uses `Depends(get_current_user)`.
`user_id` is always from the verified JWT `sub` claim — never from the request body.

## Rules (non-negotiable)
- No ORM — Supabase Python client only
- No hardcoded secrets — all config from env vars (.env, never committed)
- user_id always from JWT, never from request body
- Return 404 (not 403) for owned-resource-not-found
- Return 401 for missing/invalid JWT
- CORS: allow http://localhost:3000

## Environment Variables (from .env)
- `SUPABASE_URL`
- `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` — secret/service-role key, not publishable; bypasses RLS
- `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET`

## Out of Scope (Phase 1)
Do not implement: frontend wiring, S3, Lambda, Bedrock, Comprehend.
